assignments.description:
Open note, open tech, but not open friend, not open Discord, etc. Do the exam on your own. Earn your grade. Learn the material. It does you no good to get a good grade without knowing the material.

You will be presented one question at a time which you must answer or skip before going on. Once you answer or skip, you cannot revisit the question. 

For multiple answer questions, you must provide all the correct answers to receive credit. No partial credit. This is how it is on the certification exams.

By starting this exam, you affirm that:

As members of the Clemson University community, we have inherited Thomas Green Clemson’s vision of this institution as a “high seminary of learning.” Fundamental to this vision is a mutual commitment to truthfulness, honor, and responsibility, without which we cannot earn the trust and respect of others. Furthermore, we recognize that academic dishonesty detracts from the value of a Clemson degree. Therefore, we shall not tolerate lying, cheating, or stealing in any form.

Students failing to follow these guidelines (plagiarism, working with others, etc.) will be referred to the appropriate administrator(s) for academic dishonesty. For exams with open-ended questions, answers will be checked for similarity.
assignments.name: Exam 1 - Midterm Spring 2025
assignments.lock_explanation: This assignment was locked Feb 26 at 5:30pm.

assignments.description:
You will work in teams of 3 (roughly) and submit a presentation based upon the information provided in GroupMidtermProject.pptx . Be sure to review the Notes included in the Powerpoint file. 

At a high-level, a hypothetical medical startup company (TigerMed) has hired your group to design an infrastructure solution in AWS based upon information provided to you about an existing operational, on-premise solution. 

Your group will submit a presentation that addresses the following topics (at a minimum):

  • Identity and Access Management (5 points)
  • Network Architecture and Security (5 points)
  • Compute and Storage Resources (5 points)
  • High Availability and Scalability (5 points)
  • Auditing (5 points)

There are useful worksheets to use in GroupMidtermProject.pptx  

Your presentation should instill confidence in the medical startup company. The presentation should consider all the requirements provided, be professional, and well-reasoned.

Your submission should be a PowerPoint presentation or slides in a PDF file. Optionally, you can submit a video presentation of your group delivering the presentation. Each student in the group will receive the same grade (with exceptions).

Again, do not do the lab exercise after you start the lab. Once the lab environment is created, click the AWS button at the top to go to the AWS Management Console. Examine the lab environment using the AWS Management Console to answer the questions.

Good luck!

assignments.description:
Hi - To keep things simple, but true to the idea that graduate students have to do more in joint classes, here's what I'd like each of you graduate students to do individually. Do the project on your own without assistance from friends or Discord. Earn your grade and learn something valuable.
 
Complete the following lab exercises in the AWS Academy Cloud Architecting class and submit your work (there's a Submit button) on AWS Academy for each lab exercise.
 
Module 6 Challenge Lab - Migrating a Database to Amazon RDS (25 points)
Module 7 Challenge Lab - Creating a VPC Networking Environment for the Cafe  (56 points)
Capstone Project (35 points) - the project deliverables include a diagram and a written summary of the design decisions you made. Attach them to this assignment.
 
Keep in mind that these lab exercises are far more involved than the typical lab exercises. Be sure to plan your time accordingly.
